properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 11 at 3:33PM CST until February 13 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...ACCUMULATING SNOW...BLOWING SNOW AND DANGEROUS WIND CHILLS FOR
THE SOUTH SHORE WEDNESDAY THROUGH THURSDAY MORNING...

.Snow and lake effect snow will impact the South Shore Wednesday
through Thursday morning. The greatest snowfall accumulations of 5
to 9 inches are forecast for the northern portions of Bayfield,
Iron, and Ashland counties, with lesser amounts of 4 to 6 inches
elsewhere. Blowing snow and dangerous wind chills to 35 below are
also expected.

* WHAT...Snow and lake effect snow expected. Total snow
accumulations of 4 to 6 inches, with higher amounts of 5 to 9
inches for northern Iron, Ashland and Bayfield counties.

* WHERE...Douglas, Bayfield, Ashland and Iron Counties. This
includes the Tribal Lands of the Red Cliff Band and the Bad
River Reservation.

* WHEN...From 6 AM Wednesday to noon CST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning or evening commute. The
dangerously cold wind chills as low as 35 below zero could cause
frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 10 minutes. Blowing
snow will further reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
Road conditions can also be found at 511wi.gov for Wisconsin.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM WEDNESDAY TO NOON CST THURSDAY
